  "Name": "Operator groups no longer protected by AdminSDHolder and SDProp",
  "ScriptName": "DwAdminSDExMaskSet",
  "ShortName": "SI000053",
  "Description": "This indicator checks if dwAdminSDExMask mask on dsHeuristics has been set, which indicates a change to the SDProp behavior that could compromise security. Certain groups can be removed from SDProp protection with this setting.",
  "CategoryId": "3",
  "Weight": 5,
  "Severity": "Warning",
  "Schedule": "1d",
  "Impact": 5,
  "LikelihoodOfCompromise": "<p>Normally the default behavior for AdminSDHolder SDProp should be left intact. If its behavior is modified, this could indicate an attempt at defense evasion.</p>\n        <h3>References</h3>\n      <p><a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/openspecs/windows_protocols/ms-adts/e5899be4-862e-496f-9a38-33950617d2c5\">6.1.1.2.4.1.2 dSHeuristics</a></p>\n      <p><a href=\"https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/uploads/ad_checklist.html#vuln_dsheuristics_bad\">Dangerous dsHeuristics settings | ANSSI</a></p>",
